This installation is set up to be managed by pipenv.

(0) If you do not have pipenv, install it.
On a Mac with homebrew, "brew install pipenv" should work.

(1) Run "make pipenv_setup" to install all dependencies
and then put yourself into a pipenv shell.

(2) To install pypy3 with homebrew, run "brew install pypy3"

If you're using some other package manager, try "pip install <packagename>"
